Outfielder Scott Hairston agreed to
a one-year contract with the  New York Mets , the Major League
Baseball team said.  Terms of the agreement werenâ€™t released yesterday. The deal
is worth $1.1 million, the  Associated Press  reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Hairston, 31, batted .235 with eight doubles, one triple,
seven home runs and 24 runs batted in during 79 games with the
Mets last season.  Hairston has hit 75 career home runs and driven in 222 runs
in 643 major league games with Arizona, San Diego, Oakland and
